description._content: Note; Holden 48/215 or FX model, "Australia's own car". Holden's business dates from 1856 and it became a car body manufacturer, building on chassis imported chiefly from England or the US. In 1931 it was taken over by General Motors, becoming GMH. In 1948 this model based on a small Chevrolet became the first Australian designed and built car. Some later models like the Monaro were so popular that they were exported to the US.
